			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well Syris im afraid that wood-elves cant use this weapon since its Paladin only and they cant be Paladins. And no there is no lvl requirement on the quest.  The Testimony and Note to Brother Hayle can be obtained at lvl 1, but i wouldnt recommend it, wait till about 10 or 15 or so.  However, to get the hilt, you must defeat Xioctil, a lvl 40-50ish troll shadowknight who resides in Mistmore Castle.  He himself is not the hardest part of it though.  Getting to him is no easy task even for a lvl 50, and this zone is infamous for its trains, you know what i mean if you've been there.  Next, to get testimony from Sir Lucan to get the Brilliant Sword of Faith, you will need quite a well-balanced, lvl 50 group.  He can duel wield and double attack for around 120 damage, and has his 3 Paladin buddies around to lay hands him, also he has incredible amounts of hit points and dies twice.  The best strategy for beating him appears to be to have one person with sow go to the guardhouse to pull him while the rest of the group waits at the zone to east commons.  That person will zone, and another member or two will then repeatedly hail Lucan to keep him immobile.  Do this until all of Lucan's cronies return to the city.  Then you can begin to fight Lucan himself.  I may only be a lvl 20 Paladin(and this is my only char and i have no high lvl friends to twink me), but i know this information to be true, i for one enjoy the thrill of earning things in this game, including the things i know.  So if you need help with anything, send me a tell sometime and ill be more than happy to help as a noble Paladin of Mithaniel Marr.<BR>
<BR>
Rhaurc<BR>
Solusek Ro
